description:
Right bank of Wolf Creek Glacier, St. Elias Range, between Base Camp, 1941 and mouth of Wolf Creek.  
[On sheet of original notes attached to card]:  3 miles east (downstream) of base camp on Wolf Creek glacier St. Elias Range, Yukon Territory, Canada.
location: North America: Canada, Yukon Territory, St. Elias Mountains (YT)
recommendations:
2"-11/2' high. North-facing slope back of lateral moraine.
[From sheet of original notes]: North facing hill slope back of lateral moraine of Wolf Creek glacier. Tundra vegetation and other willows associated weathered, slumped Pleistocene till. Elevation about 5000' +/- ?
                                                        Low (2"-11/2 ') stragly[sic] bush, usually in open and by itself. Does not form clumps or thickets. Leaves when fresh have rather shiny apple green colour and bark is brown to green.

description:
Right bank of Wolf Creek Glacier, St. Elias Range, between Base Camp, 1941 and mouth of Wolf Creek.  
[On sheet of original notes attached to card]:  Wolf Creek, St. Elias Range, Yukon Territory - 2 miles below base camp. Elevation same as Base Camp. North facing slope 500' above Wolf Creek glacier.
location: North America: Canada, Yukon Territory, St. Elias Mountains (YT)
recommendations:
Tundra, 2' high. 
[From sheet of original notes]: North facing slope 500' above Wolf Creek glacier.  Moderate slope (15-20 degrees)  tundra and willow covered.  Weathered Pleistoceane till slope.
                                                        Low somewhat bushy willow. Here not more than 2' high. Scattered bushes, elsewhere on slope seems to be more abundant almost forming thicket.

description:
Right bank of Wolf Creek Glacier, St. Elias Range, between Base Camp, 1941 and mouth of Wolf Creek.  
[On sheet of original notes attached to card]:  Wolf Creek area of St. Elia Range, Yukon Territory, Canada.
location: North America: Canada, Yukon Territory, St. Elias Mountains (YT)
recommendations:
Gravel flat.
[From sheet of original notes]: Gravel flat immediately in front of Wolf Creek glacier terminal moraine. East exposure. Estimated elevation 4500'. 
                            Individual scraggly bushes, leaves rather noticeable green and shiny for a willow. Associated with other Willows, Alders, and cotton woods but definitely a minor part of assemblage and usual isolated bushes.
